					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You've probably considered this already, but if you just want to spin something, and you don't care about the downsides of Euler angles (gimbal lock, etc) then there's no real reason two use three euler angles as I see it. 
<br />
<br />Two will do just fine, and can get your 3D object to any arbitrary position. That will make it easier to compute the rotation matrix.</div>

